 position you will: Oversee the full suite of People Operations functions at Truss, including hiring and recruiting, employee engagement and performance management, payroll and benefits, and compensation planning. Work with Sales leads as well as Directors of Engineering, Design, Product, and Infrastructure/Security to manage staffing processes and tooling. Work closely with senior leadership to evolve our approach to cultural stewardship. Design and continually evaluate systems and processes to improve the efficiency of People Operations and its interactions with stakeholders. Provide guidance and mentorship to managers and employees on topics such as performance management, coaching, career advancement, and mechanisms for accountability. Here\u2019s what we hope you\u2019ll bring: 10+ years experience working in HR or People Operations in growing, matrixed organizations 5+ years experience in a senior leadership position Experience in consulting and / or software development environments is a plus Experience communicating according to the distinct needs of different constituencies, and ensuring that messages are accurate and of a quality and tone consistent with the organization\u2019s leadership and culture Experience successfully managing a variety of stakeholders with disparate needs and availability Experience advocating for diversity, equity and inclusion Experience working in distributed or remote work environments A willingness to seek differing opinions and collaborate across the leadership team to solve complex problems Initiative with a bias for action Effective time and project management skills with the ability to prioritize work assignments, work collaboratively with others, and adjust schedules based on changing requirements The salary range for this position is $202,000-$243,000 per year. We value inclusion and welcome diverse viewpoints. You must be eligible to work in the US. Unfortunately, we are unable to sponsor work visas at this time. We encourage all interested candidates to apply! If this job interests you but you aren\u2019t certain if you meet all of theÂ requirements, apply anyway! More Jobs Website Twitter Or view all jobs: Developer jobs Marketing jobs Product jobs Design jobs Sales jobs Support jobs & learn about: remote work Related Jobs Bilingual Healthcare Insurance Agent \u2013 Customer Service \u2013 Spanish TTEC Our purpose drives us. Our values guide us. Our humanity connects us. Experience it for yourself! Anywhere Full Time Posted 1 week ago Customer Success Sr. Manager (Product manager experience required) Aha! The World's #1 Product Roadmap & Marketing Planning Anywhere Full Time Posted 2 weeks ago Support Specialist (Bilingual Korean/English) Doist We create tools that promote a calmer, more balanced, more fulfilling way to work and live. Anywhere Full Time Posted 4 weeks ago MAIN Podcast Community Post a job Remote Work Virtual Wedding Instagram Twitter Login REMOTE JOBS Developer jobs Marketing jobs Product jobs Design jobs Sales jobs Support jobs JOBS IN YOUR CITY Los Angeles jobs New York City jobs San Francisco jobs Chicago jobs Seattle jobs Austin jobs London jobs Paris jobs Berlin jobs POST YOUR JOBS Post a job We\u2019ve helped the world\u2019s top companies hire a talented, diverse pool of job candidates \u2013 view our success stories here. Terms & Privacy Policy & hello@remotewoman.com @ 2020 RemoteWoman \u2014 All Rights Reserved My account Post a job Back to Top Marketing Developer Design Product Sales Support"
